content: k2tog tbl weave in ends and block if necessary key k = knit k2tog = knit 2 stitches together kfb = knit in front and back of same stitch one stitch increased wyif = bring yarn to front of work and slip the next stitch as if to purl from left to right needle rs = right side sl = slip as if the purl from left to right needle st s = stitch es tbl = through the back loop ws = wrong side yo = yarn over pattern by elizabeth finn copyright 2022 ravelry eafinn0 2
